{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm here today, as June said,"},{"time":2000,"text":"to talk about a project"},{"time":4000,"text":"that my twin sister and I have been doing for the past three and half years."},{"time":8000,"text":"We're crocheting a coral reef."},{"time":11000,"text":"And it's a project that we've actually"},{"time":14000,"text":"been now joined by hundreds of people around the world,"},{"time":17000,"text":"who are doing it with us. Indeed thousands of people"},{"time":20000,"text":"have actually been involved in this project,"},{"time":22000,"text":"in many of its different aspects."},{"time":24000,"text":"It's a project that now reaches across three continents,"},{"time":27000,"text":"and its roots go into the fields of mathematics,"},{"time":31000,"text":"marine biology, feminine handicraft"},{"time":34000,"text":"and environmental activism."},{"time":37000,"text":"It's true."},{"time":39000,"text":"It's also a project"},{"time":41000,"text":"that in a very beautiful way,"},{"time":43000,"text":"the development of this"},{"time":45000,"text":"has actually paralleled the evolution of life on earth,"},{"time":49000,"text":"which is a particularly lovely thing to be saying"},{"time":51000,"text":"right here in February 2009 --"},{"time":53000,"text":"which, as one of our previous speakers told us,"},{"time":55000,"text":"is the 200th anniversary"},{"time":57000,"text":"of the birth of Charles Darwin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59000,"text":"All of this I'm going to get to in the next 18 minutes, I hope."},{"time":63000,"text":"But let me first begin by showing you"},{"time":65000,"text":"some pictures of what this thing looks like."},{"time":68000,"text":"Just to give you an idea of scale,"},{"time":70000,"text":"that installation there is about six feet across,"},{"time":73000,"text":"and the tallest models are about two or three feet high."},{"time":77000,"text":"This is some more images of it."},{"time":79000,"text":"That one on the right is about five feet high."},{"time":81000,"text":"The work involves hundreds of different crochet models."},{"time":85000,"text":"And indeed there are now thousands and thousands of models that people"},{"time":88000,"text":"have contributed all over the world as part of this."},{"time":91000,"text":"The totality of this project"},{"time":93000,"text":"involves tens of thousands of hours"},{"time":95000,"text":"of human labor --"},{"time":97000,"text":"99 percent of it done by women."},{"time":99000,"text":"On the right hand side, that bit there is part of an installation"},{"time":102000,"text":"that is about 12 feet long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"My sister and I started this project in 2005"},{"time":107000,"text":"because in that year, at least in the science press,"},{"time":109000,"text":"there was a lot of talk about global warming,"},{"time":112000,"text":"and the effect that global warming was having on coral reefs."},{"time":115000,"text":"Corals are very delicate organisms,"},{"time":117000,"text":"and they are devastated by any rise in sea temperatures."},{"time":120000,"text":"It causes these vast bleaching events"},{"time":122000,"text":"that are the first signs of corals of being sick."},{"time":125000,"text":"And if the bleaching doesn't go away --"},{"time":127000,"text":"if the temperatures don't go down -- reefs start to die."},{"time":130000,"text":"A great deal of this has been happening in the Great Barrier Reef,"},{"time":133000,"text":"particularly in coral reefs all over the world."},{"time":135000,"text":"This is our invocation in crochet of a bleached reef."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"We have a new organization together called The Institute for Figuring,"},{"time":142000,"text":"which is a little organization we started"},{"time":144000,"text":"to promote, to do projects about the"},{"time":146000,"text":"aesthetic and poetic dimensions of science and mathematics."},{"time":149000,"text":"And I went and put a little announcement up on our site,"},{"time":152000,"text":"asking for people to join us in this enterprise."},{"time":154000,"text":"To our surprise, one of the first people who called"},{"time":157000,"text":"was the Andy Warhol Museum."},{"time":159000,"text":"And they said they were having an exhibition"},{"time":161000,"text":"about artists' response to global warming,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and they'd like our coral reef to be part of it."},{"time":165000,"text":"I laughed and said, \"Well we've only just started it,"},{"time":167000,"text":"you can have a little bit of it.\""},{"time":169000,"text":"So in 2007 we had an exhibition,"},{"time":172000,"text":"a small exhibition of this crochet reef."},{"time":174000,"text":"And then some people in Chicago came along and they said,"},{"time":176000,"text":"\"In late 2007, the theme of the Chicago Humanities Festival is"},{"time":181000,"text":"global warming. And we've got this 3,000 square-foot gallery"},{"time":184000,"text":"and we want you to fill it with your reef.\""},{"time":187000,"text":"And I, naively by this stage, said, \"Oh, yes, sure.\""},{"time":190000,"text":"Now I say \"naively\" because actually"},{"time":192000,"text":"my profession is as a science writer."},{"time":194000,"text":"What I do is I write books about the cultural history of physics."},{"time":197000,"text":"I've written books about the history of space,"},{"time":199000,"text":"the history of physics and religion,"},{"time":201000,"text":"and I write articles for people like the New York Times and the L.A. Times."},{"time":204000,"text":"So I had no idea what it meant to fill a 3,000 square-foot gallery."},{"time":208000,"text":"So I said yes to this proposition."},{"time":210000,"text":"And I went home, and I told my sister Christine."},{"time":212000,"text":"And she nearly had a fit"},{"time":214000,"text":"because Christine is a professor at one of"},{"time":216000,"text":"L.A.'s major art colleges, CalArts,"},{"time":219000,"text":"and she knew exactly what it meant to fill a 3,000 square-foot gallery."},{"time":222000,"text":"She thought I'd gone off my head."},{"time":225000,"text":"But she went into crochet overdrive."},{"time":227000,"text":"And to cut a long story short, eight months later"},{"time":229000,"text":"we did fill the Chicago Cultural Center's"},{"time":232000,"text":"3,000 square foot gallery."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"By this stage the project had taken on"},{"time":236000,"text":"a viral dimension of its own,"},{"time":238000,"text":"which got completely beyond us."},{"time":240000,"text":"The people in Chicago decided"},{"time":242000,"text":"that as well as exhibiting our reefs, what they wanted to do"},{"time":245000,"text":"was have the local people there make a reef."},{"time":247000,"text":"So we went and taught the techniques. We did workshops and lectures."},{"time":250000,"text":"And the people in Chicago made a reef of their own."},{"time":253000,"text":"And it was exhibited alongside ours."},{"time":255000,"text":"There were hundreds of people involved in that."},{"time":257000,"text":"We got invited to do the whole thing"},{"time":260000,"text":"in New York, and in London,"},{"time":262000,"text":"and in Los Angeles."},{"time":264000,"text":"In each of these cities, the local citizens,"},{"time":266000,"text":"hundreds and hundreds of them, have made a reef."},{"time":268000,"text":"And more and more people get involved in this,"},{"time":271000,"text":"most of whom we've never met."},{"time":273000,"text":"So the whole thing has sort of morphed"},{"time":275000,"text":"into this organic, ever-evolving creature,"},{"time":277000,"text":"that's actually gone way beyond Christine and I."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"Now some of you are sitting here thinking,"},{"time":284000,"text":"\"What planet are these people on?"},{"time":286000,"text":"Why on earth are you crocheting a reef?"},{"time":289000,"text":"Woolenness and wetness aren't exactly"},{"time":291000,"text":"two concepts that go together."},{"time":293000,"text":"Why not chisel a coral reef out of marble?"},{"time":295000,"text":"Cast it in bronze.\""},{"time":297000,"text":"But it turns out there is a very good reason"},{"time":299000,"text":"why we are crocheting it"},{"time":301000,"text":"because many organisms in coral reefs"},{"time":303000,"text":"have a very particular kind of structure."},{"time":305000,"text":"The frilly crenulated forms that you see"},{"time":307000,"text":"in corals, and kelps, and sponges and nudibranchs,"},{"time":310000,"text":"is a form of geometry known as hyperbolic geometry."},{"time":313000,"text":"And the only way that mathematicians know"},{"time":316000,"text":"how to model this structure"},{"time":318000,"text":"is with crochet. It happens to be a fact."},{"time":320000,"text":"It's almost impossible to model this structure any other way,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and it's almost impossible to do it on computers."},{"time":326000,"text":"So what is this hyperbolic geometry"},{"time":328000,"text":"that corals and sea slugs embody?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"The next few minutes is, we're all going to get raised up"},{"time":334000,"text":"to the level of a sea slug."},{"time":336000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":337000,"text":"This sort of geometry revolutionized mathematics"},{"time":340000,"text":"when it was first discovered in the 19th century."},{"time":343000,"text":"But not until 1997 did mathematicians actually understand"},{"time":346000,"text":"how they could model it."},{"time":348000,"text":"In 1997 a mathematician"},{"time":350000,"text":"at Cornell, Daina Taimina,"},{"time":352000,"text":"made the discovery that this structure"},{"time":354000,"text":"could actually be done in knitting and crochet."},{"time":356000,"text":"The first one she did was knitting."},{"time":358000,"text":"But you get too many stitches on the needle. So she quickly realized"},{"time":360000,"text":"crochet was the better thing."},{"time":362000,"text":"But what she was doing was actually making a model"},{"time":365000,"text":"of a mathematical structure, that many mathematicians"},{"time":367000,"text":"had thought it was actually impossible to model."},{"time":370000,"text":"And indeed they thought that anything like this structure"},{"time":372000,"text":"was impossible per se."},{"time":374000,"text":"Some of the best mathematicians spent hundreds of years"},{"time":376000,"text":"trying to prove that this structure was impossible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"So what is this impossible hyperbolic structure?"},{"time":382000,"text":"Before hyperbolic geometry, mathematicians knew"},{"time":384000,"text":"about two kinds of space:"},{"time":386000,"text":"Euclidean space, and spherical space."},{"time":389000,"text":"And they have different properties."},{"time":391000,"text":"Mathematicians like to characterize things by being formalist."},{"time":394000,"text":"You all have a sense of what a flat space is, Euclidean space is."},{"time":398000,"text":"But mathematicians formalize this in a particular way."},{"time":401000,"text":"And what they do is, they do it through the concept"},{"time":403000,"text":"of parallel lines."},{"time":405000,"text":"So here we have a line and a point outside the line."},{"time":408000,"text":"And Euclid said, \"How can I define parallel lines?"},{"time":411000,"text":"I ask the question, how many lines can I draw through"},{"time":414000,"text":"the point but never meet the original line?\""},{"time":416000,"text":"And you all know the answer. Does someone want to shout it out?"},{"time":419000,"text":"One. Great. Okay."},{"time":421000,"text":"That's our definition of a parallel line."},{"time":423000,"text":"It's a definition really of Euclidean space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"But there is another possibility that you all know of:"},{"time":428000,"text":"spherical space."},{"time":430000,"text":"Think of the surface of a sphere --"},{"time":432000,"text":"just like a beach ball, the surface of the Earth."},{"time":434000,"text":"I have a straight line on my spherical surface."},{"time":437000,"text":"And I have a point outside the line. How many straight lines"},{"time":439000,"text":"can I draw through the point"},{"time":441000,"text":"but never meet the original line?"},{"time":443000,"text":"What do we mean to talk about"},{"time":445000,"text":"a straight line on a curved surface?"},{"time":448000,"text":"Now mathematicians have answered that question."},{"time":451000,"text":"They've understood there is a generalized concept"},{"time":453000,"text":"of straightness, it's called a geodesic."},{"time":455000,"text":"And on the surface of a sphere,"},{"time":457000,"text":"a straight line is the biggest possible circle you can draw."},{"time":460000,"text":"So it's like the equator or the lines of longitude."},{"time":464000,"text":"So we ask the question again,"},{"time":466000,"text":"\"How many straight lines can I draw through the point,"},{"time":468000,"text":"but never meet the original line?\""},{"time":470000,"text":"Does someone want to guess?"},{"time":473000,"text":"Zero. Very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"Now mathematicians thought that was the only alternative."},{"time":477000,"text":"It's a bit suspicious isn't it? There is two answers to the question so far,"},{"time":480000,"text":"Zero and one."},{"time":482000,"text":"Two answers? There may possibly be a third alternative."},{"time":484000,"text":"To a mathematician if there are two answers,"},{"time":486000,"text":"and the first two are zero and one,"},{"time":488000,"text":"there is another number that immediately suggests itself"},{"time":490000,"text":"as the third alternative."},{"time":492000,"text":"Does anyone want to guess what it is?"},{"time":495000,"text":"Infinity. You all got it right. Exactly."},{"time":498000,"text":"There is, there's a third alternative."},{"time":500000,"text":"This is what it looks like."},{"time":502000,"text":"There's a straight line, and there is an infinite number of lines"},{"time":505000,"text":"that go through the point and never meet the original line."},{"time":507000,"text":"This is the drawing."},{"time":509000,"text":"This nearly drove mathematicians bonkers"},{"time":511000,"text":"because, like you, they're sitting there feeling bamboozled."},{"time":514000,"text":"Thinking, how can that be? You're cheating. The lines are curved."},{"time":517000,"text":"But that's only because I'm projecting it onto a"},{"time":519000,"text":"flat surface."},{"time":521000,"text":"Mathematicians for several hundred years"},{"time":523000,"text":"had to really struggle with this."},{"time":525000,"text":"How could they see this?"},{"time":527000,"text":"What did it mean to actually have a physical model"},{"time":530000,"text":"that looked like this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":532000,"text":"It's a bit like this: imagine that we'd only ever encountered Euclidean space."},{"time":535000,"text":"Then our mathematicians come along"},{"time":537000,"text":"and said, \"There's this thing called a sphere,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and the lines come together at the north and south pole.\""},{"time":541000,"text":"But you don't know what a sphere looks like."},{"time":543000,"text":"And someone that comes along and says, \"Look here's a ball.\""},{"time":546000,"text":"And you go, \"Ah! I can see it. I can feel it."},{"time":548000,"text":"I can touch it. I can play with it.\""},{"time":551000,"text":"And that's exactly what happened"},{"time":553000,"text":"when Daina Taimina"},{"time":555000,"text":"in 1997, showed that you could crochet models"},{"time":559000,"text":"in hyperbolic space."},{"time":561000,"text":"Here is this diagram in crochetness."},{"time":564000,"text":"I've stitched Euclid's parallel postulate on to the surface."},{"time":568000,"text":"And the lines look curved."},{"time":570000,"text":"But look, I can prove to you that they're straight"},{"time":573000,"text":"because I can take any one of these lines,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and I can fold along it."},{"time":578000,"text":"And it's a straight line."},{"time":580000,"text":"So here, in wool,"},{"time":583000,"text":"through a domestic feminine art,"},{"time":585000,"text":"is the proof that the most famous postulate"},{"time":587000,"text":"in mathematics is wrong."},{"time":590000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"And you can stitch all sorts of mathematical"},{"time":598000,"text":"theorems onto these surfaces."},{"time":601000,"text":"The discovery of hyperbolic space ushered in the field of mathematics"},{"time":604000,"text":"that is called non-Euclidean geometry."},{"time":606000,"text":"And this is actually the field of mathematics"},{"time":608000,"text":"that underlies general relativity"},{"time":610000,"text":"and is actually ultimately going to show us"},{"time":612000,"text":"about the shape of the universe."},{"time":614000,"text":"So there is this direct line"},{"time":616000,"text":"between feminine handicraft,"},{"time":618000,"text":"Euclid and general relativity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"Now, I said that mathematicians thought that this was impossible."},{"time":624000,"text":"Here's two creatures who've never heard of Euclid's parallel postulate --"},{"time":628000,"text":"didn't know it was impossible to violate,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and they're simply getting on with it."},{"time":632000,"text":"They've been doing it for hundreds of millions of years."},{"time":636000,"text":"I once asked the mathematicians why it was"},{"time":638000,"text":"that mathematicians thought this structure was impossible"},{"time":641000,"text":"when sea slugs have been doing it since the Silurian age."},{"time":644000,"text":"Their answer was interesting."},{"time":646000,"text":"They said, \"Well I guess there aren't that many mathematicians"},{"time":648000,"text":"sitting around looking at sea slugs.\""},{"time":650000,"text":"And that's true. But it also goes deeper than that."},{"time":653000,"text":"It also says a whole lot of things"},{"time":655000,"text":"about what mathematicians thought mathematics was,"},{"time":658000,"text":"what they thought it could and couldn't do,"},{"time":660000,"text":"what they thought it could and couldn't represent."},{"time":662000,"text":"Even mathematicians, who in some sense"},{"time":664000,"text":"are the freest of all thinkers,"},{"time":666000,"text":"literally couldn't see"},{"time":668000,"text":"not only the sea slugs around them,"},{"time":670000,"text":"but the lettuce on their plate --"},{"time":672000,"text":"because lettuces, and all those curly vegetables,"},{"time":674000,"text":"they also are embodiments of hyperbolic geometry."},{"time":678000,"text":"And so in some sense they literally,"},{"time":681000,"text":"they had such a symbolic view of mathematics,"},{"time":683000,"text":"they couldn't actually see what was going on"},{"time":686000,"text":"on the lettuce in front of them."},{"time":689000,"text":"It turns out that the natural world is full of hyperbolic wonders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693000,"text":"And so, too, we've discovered"},{"time":695000,"text":"that there is an infinite taxonomy"},{"time":697000,"text":"of crochet hyperbolic creatures."},{"time":699000,"text":"We started out, Chrissy and I and our contributors,"},{"time":702000,"text":"doing the simple mathematically perfect models."},{"time":704000,"text":"But we found that when we deviated from the specific"},{"time":708000,"text":"setness of the mathematical code"},{"time":711000,"text":"that underlies it -- the simple algorithm"},{"time":713000,"text":"crochet three, increase one --"},{"time":715000,"text":"when we deviated from that and made embellishments to the code,"},{"time":718000,"text":"the models immediately started to look more natural."},{"time":722000,"text":"And all of our contributors, who are an amazing"},{"time":724000,"text":"collection of people around the world,"},{"time":726000,"text":"do their own embellishments."},{"time":728000,"text":"As it were, we have this ever-evolving,"},{"time":730000,"text":"crochet taxonomic tree of life."},{"time":732000,"text":"Just as the morphology"},{"time":734000,"text":"and the complexity of life on earth is never ending,"},{"time":736000,"text":"little embellishments and complexifications"},{"time":739000,"text":"in the DNA code"},{"time":741000,"text":"lead to new things like giraffes, or orchids --"},{"time":744000,"text":"so too, do little embellishments in the crochet code"},{"time":747000,"text":"lead to new and wondrous creatures"},{"time":750000,"text":"in the evolutionary tree of crochet life."},{"time":753000,"text":"So this project really has"},{"time":755000,"text":"taken on this inner organic life of its own."},{"time":758000,"text":"There is the totality of all the people who have come to it."},{"time":761000,"text":"And their individual visions,"},{"time":763000,"text":"and their engagement with this mathematical mode."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766000,"text":"We have these technologies. We use them."},{"time":768000,"text":"But why? What's at stake here? What does it matter?"},{"time":771000,"text":"For Chrissy and I, one of the things that's important here"},{"time":774000,"text":"is that these things suggest"},{"time":776000,"text":"the importance and value of embodied knowledge."},{"time":779000,"text":"We live in a society"},{"time":781000,"text":"that completely tends to valorize"},{"time":783000,"text":"symbolic forms of representation --"},{"time":785000,"text":"algebraic representations,"},{"time":787000,"text":"equations, codes."},{"time":789000,"text":"We live in a society that's obsessed"},{"time":791000,"text":"with presenting information in this way,"},{"time":793000,"text":"teaching information in this way."},{"time":796000,"text":"But through this sort of modality,"},{"time":799000,"text":"crochet, other plastic forms of play --"},{"time":803000,"text":"people can be engaged with the most abstract,"},{"time":806000,"text":"high-powered, theoretical ideas,"},{"time":808000,"text":"the kinds of ideas that normally you have to go"},{"time":810000,"text":"to university departments to study in higher mathematics,"},{"time":813000,"text":"which is where I first learned about hyperbolic space."},{"time":816000,"text":"But you can do it through playing with material objects."},{"time":820000,"text":"One of the ways that we've come to think about this"},{"time":822000,"text":"is that what we're trying to do with the Institute for Figuring"},{"time":825000,"text":"and projects like this, we're trying to have"},{"time":827000,"text":"kindergarten for grown-ups."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"And kindergarten was actually a very formalized"},{"time":831000,"text":"system of education,"},{"time":833000,"text":"established by a man named Friedrich Froebel,"},{"time":835000,"text":"who was a crystallographer in the 19th century."},{"time":837000,"text":"He believed that the crystal was the model"},{"time":839000,"text":"for all kinds of representation."},{"time":841000,"text":"He developed a radical alternative system"},{"time":844000,"text":"of engaging the smallest children"},{"time":846000,"text":"with the most abstract ideas"},{"time":848000,"text":"through physical forms of play."},{"time":850000,"text":"And he is worthy of an entire talk on his own right."},{"time":852000,"text":"The value of education"},{"time":854000,"text":"is something that Froebel championed,"},{"time":857000,"text":"through plastic modes of play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859000,"text":"We live in a society now"},{"time":861000,"text":"where we have lots of think tanks,"},{"time":863000,"text":"where great minds go to think about the world."},{"time":866000,"text":"They write these great symbolic treatises"},{"time":868000,"text":"called books, and papers,"},{"time":870000,"text":"and op-ed articles."},{"time":872000,"text":"We want to propose, Chrissy and I,"},{"time":874000,"text":"through The Institute for Figuring, another alternative way of doing things,"},{"time":877000,"text":"which is the play tank."},{"time":880000,"text":"And the play tank, like the think tank,"},{"time":882000,"text":"is a place where people can go"},{"time":884000,"text":"and engage with great ideas."},{"time":886000,"text":"But what we want to propose,"},{"time":888000,"text":"is that the highest levels of abstraction,"},{"time":890000,"text":"things like mathematics, computing, logic, etc. --"},{"time":893000,"text":"all of this can be engaged with,"},{"time":895000,"text":"not just through purely cerebral algebraic"},{"time":897000,"text":"symbolic methods,"},{"time":899000,"text":"but by literally, physically playing with ideas."},{"time":903000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":905000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}